text: The whiteband goby (Paedovaricus imswe) is a species of ray-finned fish from the family Gobiidae. It has only been recorded from two sites, the Eleuthera Islands in the Bahamas and Carrie Bow Cay in Belize. ==References== Category:Gobiidae Category:Monotypic fish genera Category:Fish described in 1981
title: Whiteband goby
